title: ‘Far from over’: Pressure on King to 'go further' with ‘diabolical’ Andrew situation
description: Sky News contributor Sophie Elsworth discusses the continued royal fallout over Andrew Mountbatten Windsor’s ties to Jeffrey Epstein.  “There is a huge push for this to go further ... this is far from over,” she told Sky News host Chris Kenny.  “The pressure is on the King to ensure that all is done to handle this situation, which has been diabolical for the Royal Family.”

title: Andrew to move out of Royal Lodge in the new year to avoid ‘awkward exchange’
description: Sky News contributor Sophie Elsworth claims reports suggest Andrew Mountbatten Windsor won’t move out of Royal Lodge until the new year to avoid an “awkward exchange” with the Royal Family during the Christmas festivities.  “Now we know that Andrew will be moving out of the Royal Lodge. Reports are that will be in the new year to avoid that awkward exchange that would happen when the Royal Family are in Sandringham at Christmas,” she told Sky News host Chris Kenny.  “But overnight, we were told that perhaps it could be sooner that he moves there, so we’re waiting to see what happens there, but he’s name is definitely tarnished.”

title: NT Chief Minister calls on federal government to reclaim Port of Darwin
description: The Northern Territory's Chief Minister Lia Finocchiaro is calling on the federal government to return the Port of Darwin to Australian hands.

title: Democrats blasted for holding struggling Americans to ransom voting to continue shutdown
description: US President Donald Trump laid the blame for the government shutdown solely on the Democrats during a '60 Minutes interview.  Trump went on to say he would not be "extorted" by the Democrats to end the shutdown.  The president then took aim at Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer, calling him a "basket case".  Trump's comments come as the government shutdown has reached day 34, one day short of the record.  President Trump flamed the Democrats for voting against the Republicans 14 times to open the country.

title: Barnaby Joyce speaks out on the Nationals scrapping net zero
description: Nationals MP Barnaby Joyce joins Sky News Australia to discuss the party scrapping its net zero policy.

title: ‘Definition of insanity’: Credlin blasts Coalition for ‘drinking the climate Kool-Aid’
description: Sky News host Peta Credlin has blasted the Opposition for “drinking the climate Kool-Aid”.  “It’s the definition of insanity to do the same thing over and over again and yet expect a different result,” Ms Credlin said.  “This is what has happened to the federal Opposition since they drank the climate Kool-Aid and fell into line with Scott Morrison’s demand that they embrace net zero.”

title: ‘Control the disaster’: Calls for Nigerian government to help end Christian persecution
description: Former Labor senator Stephen Conroy discusses United States President Donald Trump ordering the Pentagon to prepare for possible action in Nigeria.  “Firstly, I want to say to the hard left in Australia, that’s what genocide looks like, not what went on in Israel and the Hamas conflict,” Mr Conroy told Sky News Australia.   “That’s what a real genocide looks like.  “[Trump] doesn’t need to put boots on the ground to absolutely change the landscape, so let’s hope that it is not needed, let’s hope that the Nigerian government takes some sort of control of the disaster that is occurring.”

title: Billie Eilish torn to shreds for being a 'hypocrite' following billionaire remarks
description: Sky News host Caleb Bond rips into “hypocrite” US singer Billie Eilish after she lashed out at billionaires and urged them to give away their wealth.  “She seems to be a bit of a socialist, despite the fact that she has millions and millions of dollars in the bank,” Mr Bond said.   “It’s okay to be a multimillionaire, but if you’re a billionaire, that’s bad.  “If you’re giving away 20 per cent of $US50 million, I don’t think you can tell me you’re such a wonderful, virtuous person, because why not give away 99 per cent of it.  “Just go and quietly give your money away. Why does the world need to know you’re giving your money away?”

title: New polls show overwhelming support for immigration cuts in Australia
description: New polling suggests more Australians are supporting immigration cuts as Opposition Leader Sussan Ley faces mounting pressure to take a tougher approach.  According to Newspoll in The Australian, 64 per cent of voters want fewer immigrants.  About 10 per cent want more immigrants, while around a quarter of those surveyed support current levels.

title: Trump feels ‘badly’ for British Royal Family over Andrew-Epstein scandal
description: US President Donald Trump says he feels bad for the UK Royal Family after disgraced former prince Andrew had his titles removed.  The US President appeared to suggest the renewed pressure on the Royal Family linked to the convicted sex offender Jeffrey Epstein was unfair.  Along with losing his titles, the former prince will now move out of the Royal Lodge and move into one of the royal residences of King Charles.

title: ‘Absolute idiotic buffoon’: Harrison Ford brutally savaged over ‘mad raving’ about Trump
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi has slammed Harrison Ford over the American actor’s recent anti-Donald Trump rant.  “Lot of what he says seems to be the mad ravings of a first-year art student. Isn’t he too old for this?” she said.  “I mean, really, Harrison Ford, what an absolute idiotic buffoon you are.”

title: Whoopi Goldberg mocked for temper tantrum after forced to clarify Trump autopen joke
description: ‘The View’ co-host Whoopi Goldberg has been roasted after she snapped on live television while speaking about US President Donald Trump.  On Monday, the co-hosts discussed Trump’s pardoning of Binance’s founder Changpeng "CZ" Zhao and the president’s ’60 Minutes’ interview.  During the discussion, Goldberg made a joke about Trump using an autopen to pardon the founder of the world’s largest crypto exchange.  Goldberg responded to fellow co-host Sunny Hostin’s remarks about Trump’s pardon, joking that the president didn’t know who Zhao was “because he used an autopen”.  Later in the show, Hostin was seen writing on a paper before passing it to Goldberg as she was speaking.  Goldberg then ripped up the note card and argued she did not need to clarify her comments about Trump.

title: ‘Borderline demonic’: Nicki Minaj cops intense backlash from ‘deranged’ lefties for Trump praise
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi has blasted “deranged” lefties over the intense backlash against singer Nicki Minaj for thanking President Donald Trump for taking the persecution against Christians in Nigeria seriously.  “I mean, who could possibly read that and be upset,” she said.  “I mean utterly deranged with hatred for Donald Trump must you be that you can’t acknowledge the fact that there are women and children being slaughtered just because they’re Christian.  “It’s borderline demonic when you read some of those comments.”

title: Transgender Democrat congresswoman schooled by CNN host over government shutdown
description: CNN has spectacularly turned on the Democrats over the government shutdown that has now been going for 34 days.   CNN host Brianna Keiler schooled transgender Democrat congresswoman Sarah McBride on the Democrats role in ensuring the government remains shut.

title: Trump backs Andrew Cuomo in NYC mayoral race and warns of 'communist' Mamdani
description: US President Donald Trump has officially endorsed Andrew Cuomo in the New York City mayoral race while slamming Zohran Mamdani as a “communist”.  Trump said on Truth Social that it would be “highly unlikely” that he would send federal funds to New York City if Mamdani becomes mayor.  “It is my obligation to run the Nation, and it is my strong conviction that New York City will be a Complete and Total Economic and Social Disaster should Mamdani win,” Trump wrote.  “I would much rather see a Democrat, who has had a Record of Success, WIN, than a Communist with no experience and a Record of COMPLETE AND TOTAL FAILURE.”  In an extended interview with 60 Minutes, the President said he would choose a “bad Democrat” over a “Communist” every single time.
